definition:
A man living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 2Ki.18.13; 
 father of: Adrammelech (H0152H), Sharezer (H8272) and Esarhaddon (H0634); also called Sargon at Isa.20.1;
Another name of san.che.riv (סַנְחֵרִיב "Sennacherib" H5576) 
 § Sargon = "prince of the sun"
 king of Assyria, son of Shalmaneser, and father of Sennacherib; ruled from 721-702 BC; conqueror of Samaria
